            . I am a <rs id="t18220417-192-viclabel1010" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220417-192-victim1773 t18220417-192-viclabel1010"></join>, and live in Mason's-alley, Basinghall-street. The prisoner worked for me, and I lent him all these tools, but one plane; but did not allow him to take them off the premises. He left me before he had finished his job. I met him three weeks afterward, in Paul's-alley, Whitecross-street, with a quantity of pawnbroker's duplicates in his hand, I asked him to let me see them; he ran off, I followed: he was secured, and fifty-four duplicates found on him, some of which were for my tools.</p>
